🎉Pika World Breakfast Market Update 23 Aug 2023🎉🎲Thin trading volume in swinging session💰It's late August and trading volume remains low as traders are still soaking into the vibe of summer. Today we will receive the much anticipated earnings from Nvidia in the after-hours.🎢Retail sectors showed consumer preferences in spending🍣The store chains tend to be the last group to report earnings because their fiscal year tends to end in January instead of December. The holiday season is often the highlight for retailers in December.We have seen results from Macy  Lowes and Dick's Sporting goods. The key similarity is a decline in earnings compared to a year ago. This should not come as a surpirse gien that we have seen a strong consumer spending ths year  yet there is a switch of spending away fromj goods to experiences.So one can look at the restaurant food prices   airfares and even concert tickets. They are in much higher demand.🍱Discretionary spending in physical goods declining💸Indeed  as Macy's CEO mentioned  there appeared to be a pullback in psending on their discretionary cagetories and the shift twoards experience and services are still ongoing.📪What's on the menu today?📖1) 9.45pm : S&P Global Composite PMI2) 10 pm : New Home SalesIt is 23 August  Wednesday  9 am in Singapore and 9 pm in New York. It has been yet another swinging trade day. We could not offload our key positions and will be improving our capital base to ride through the volatile August as we do see heighten swings ahead of us.Have a splendid day at work and in school!Cheers Pika Nat.🧃
